  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether daily use of a lower limb venous-return
      assist device, &quot;Venowave', improves leg symptoms, ability to perform activities of daily
      living, and quality of life in subjects with severe PTS.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Eligible consenting patients will be randomly allocated to receive either the veno-device
      (active or placebo for 8 weeks and crossed over for a further 8 weeks (active or placebo)
      following a 4 week 'wash out' period.( A randomized controlled 'crossover' study}
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
